15 of the Board of Trustees, and recipient of the foundation's highest honor, the William
16 Rosenberg Leadership Award; and
17 WHEREAS, he has further worked to advocate for the needs of small businesses and
18 franchising, serving as a delegate representing the State of Texas at the Third White House
19 Conference on Small Business, testifying before committees of the United States Senate and
20 House of Representatives, and actively participating in IFA's legislative and advocacy
21 efforts; and
22 WHEREAS, he has contributed significantly to philanthropic and community initiatives,
23 serving on the Board of Trustees for the Leukemia & Lymphoma Society, supporting
24 educational initiatives such as the Hakeem Olajuwon BEST Campaign, and serving on
25 numerous advisory and nonprofit boards; and
26 WHEREAS, his leadership, innovation, and dedication to the franchise industry have left a
27 lasting impact, making it abundantly fitting and proper that he be appropriately honored.
28 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
29 recognize and commend Lawrence J. "Doc" Cohen for his many outstanding career
30 contributions to the franchise industry as well as extend best wishes for future health and
31 happiness.
32 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
33 to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to Lawrence J. "Doc"
34 Cohen.
